id: pm-psy1
title: "Scripting contract: documented and test-gated guarantees for exit codes, stdout/stderr stream discipline, and stable machine-readable field names"
description: "Contract child of the composability story: scripts can only be reliable if the shell-facing behavior is promised, not incidental. Today exit codes and stdout/stderr split are unspecified; review #11/#12 hit real cases where errors on stderr made failures look like empty results (search --format). Duplicate check: docs items (pm-ds3b SDK reference) cover the programmatic surface, not the shell contract."
type: Task
